sentences: Selah Sue (born Sanne Greet A. Putseys, 3 May 1989) is a Belgian musician and songwriter.
Her debut album, Selah Sue (2011) was a major success, selling over 720,000 copies in Europe, 320,000 in France alone.
In 2011, she has had chart success with the hit singles "Raggamuffin", "Crazy Vibes" and "This World".
In 2011, Selah Sue won a European Border Breakers Award (EBBA).
In January 2012 during the EBBA award ceremony she was presented with the EBBA Public Choice Award.
On 28 August 2012, her debut album was also released in the United States, where the album received positive reviews.
More than 400,000 downloads were counted in one week.
Rolling Stone magazine named Selah Sue as one of the new faces of 2012.
Sue's first EP was released in January 2009, under the title Black Part Love.
From September 2008 until August 2009, Selah Sue received some curricular guidance from the Belgian musical theater, Ancienne Belgique.
From September 2008 until August 2009, Selah Sue received some curricular guidance from the Belgian musical theater, Ancienne Belgique.
In 2009, Selah Sue attended the stages of the North Sea Jazz Festival and Lowlands.
In 2010, she played most of the biggest festivals in Belgium, including Les Nuits Botaniques, Les Ardentes, Dour Festival, Lokerse Feesten, Couleur Caf√© and Pukkelpop.
Her second EP, Raggamuffin, was released in October 2010.
On 8 November 2010 she played a support appearance for Prince on his Sportpaleis concert.
On 4 March 2011, Selah Sue released her eponymous debut album.
On 10 December 2011, she won three prizes at the Flemish Music Industry Awards.
On 20 October 2012, Selah Sue played at the royal wedding in Luxembourg.
On 27 October 2014, Selah Sue released a new song, "Alone".
She was nominated for 3 prizes at the 2015 Music Industry Awards.
Selah Sue co-wrote Belgium's Eurovision Song Contest 2016 entry, "What's the Pressure" performed by Laura Tesoro.
In December 2016 "Bang Bang", a collaboration by DJ Fresh and Diplo, was released and featured vocals by Selah Sue.
In 2020, after a hiatus of 5 years, Selah Sue released the EP "Bedroom" on 15 May.

In 2020, after a hiatus of 5 years, Selah Sue released the EP "Bedroom" on 15 May.
The song "You" was released as the first official single of the EP on 17 April 2020 and was dedicated to her family.
In May 2014 Selah Sue made public that she has been struggling with depression in the Flemish talkshow "Reyers Laat".
She admitted that she has been using medication since she was 18 years old.
She stated that antidepressants helped her to be the person she is now and that it helped her to achieve her success.
In 2016 she was the godmother of "Te Gek!?
In October 2016, Selah Sue announced through a video on Facebook that she was expecting her first child.
In March 2017, she announced that her first son, Seth, had been born.
In March 2019 her second son Mingus was born. .
In 2021 she stopped antidepressants and started with using magic truffles (VRTelevision 26/1/2022 and her new single "Pills").
